Four more people have died from Covid-19, and another 142 positive cases have been recorded, bringing the overall tally to 3 300. There have been, however, 1 055 recoveries, the Department of Health says. The department says 121 510 people have been tested, about two-thirds of that in the public sector. Gauteng still remains the epicentre, with 1 170 cases, followed by the Western Cape with 940 and KwaZulu-Natal with 639. https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/coronavirus-all-the-latest-news-about-covid-19-in-south-africa-and-the-world-20200312